data.description: Rancher style home with a massive eat-in style kitchen. 34 cabinets and drawers in the kitchen alone. 7 closets throughout the house.  The basement boasts even more storage! There is a separate coffee/tea area that does not take from any of the other kitchen space. Beyond the main kitchen area is a dining area big enough to house at least a 6 seater table without even obstructing the walkway to the bay window. The kitchen has three windows and two doors so it is well lit even by the moon light. The sunlight continues throughout the with large windows in every room. A wood burning stove in the living room can easily heat the entire house if you choose. The original formal dining room between the kitchen and living room now serves as an office, small library or den. The full basement features a bar/entertainment area with a wood burning stove and plenty of room for pool tables. The other side of the basement contains the laundry area, a kitchenette, a workshop and shelving for ample storage. The septic system was completely replaced in 2019. Almost all of the plumbing has been updated. The Agricultural Center, Antietam Battle Field, Antietam Recreation, Premium Outlets, C&O Canal, shopping and dinning all within a short distance. More updates coming soon!   *January 7th open house canceled due to inclement weather* If you are able to get here safely, please feel free to request a showing.
